# IBM Watsonx Integration

CarbonSense is powered by IBM Watsonx for foundation models, embedding generation, and AI services.

## Foundation Models

The system leverages various IBM Watsonx models:

- For reasoning and generation: granite models
- For embeddings: slate models with different parameter sizes
- For specialized tasks: task-specific foundation models

## Embedding Models

Three primary embedding models are used:

- **30M Parameter Model**: [ibm/slate-30m-english-rtrvr-v2](mdc:Embeddings/Embeddings_30m/) (384-dimensional embeddings)
- **125M Parameter Model**: [ibm/slate-125m-english-rtrvr-v2](mdc:Embeddings/Embeddings_125m/) (768-dimensional embeddings)
- **Granite Model**: [ibm/granite-embedding-278m-multilingual](mdc:Embeddings/Embeddings_granite/) (768-dimensional embeddings)

## Service Integration

IBM Watsonx services are integrated into the CarbonSense platform:

- Watsonx service implementation: [src/carbonsense/services/watsonx_service.py](mdc:src/carbonsense/services/watsonx_service.py)
- IBM Cloud SDK configuration: [src/carbonsense/config/ibm_cloud.py](mdc:src/carbonsense/config/ibm_cloud.py)
- Authentication handling: [src/carbonsense/utils/auth.py](mdc:src/carbonsense/utils/auth.py)

The system uses IBM Cloud Object Storage (COS) for efficient file operations and data management.
